* Tech experiences that we enjoy are made so everything is as frictionless as possible.
* This is often exploited by bad corporations that put profit over people's health.
* External systems made to introduce friction when wanting to access a distracting app (forcing a X-second wait, requiring solving small logic puzzles, etc...), or during its usage (nudges telling you not to waste time), can reduce bad or useless screen time, without actually making the user feel like they are restricted (unlike what forced time limitations do).
